      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:30:3",
      "text": [
        " قُلْتُ لِأَبِي جَعْفَرٍ ( عليه السلام ) أَعْوَرُ فَقَأَ عَيْنَ صَحِيحٍ فَقَالَ تُفْقَأُ عَيْنُهُ قَالَ قُلْتُ يَبْقَى أَعْمَى قَالَ الْحَقُّ أَعْمَاهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Najran, from Aasim Bin Humeyd, from Muhammad Bin Qays who said, ",
          "‘I said to Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup>, ‘A one-eye man blinded an eye of a correct one’. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘His eye would be blinded’. I said, ‘He would remain as blind’. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘It is the right (of the victim) who has been blinded’."
        ]
      }
    }
